Short Sales

March 11, 2021

Introduction

GameStop (GME) and some Cannibis stocks have been heavily shorted since late January,2021 (GME short interest over 100% in late January),which squeezed out big short sellers like hedge fund company Melvin Capital.It is worthwhile to watch shorted stocks as it can affect market volatility.This document provides a brief summary of short-selling activities for active common shares listed in AQL, CSE, TSX and TSXV Canadian exchanges. Data included in this document are updated bi-monthly.

 

Data

Data is calculated from IIROC and Refinitiv:

  • IIROC — Number of short positions are collected to calculate short interest(% of float) and days to cover.1
  • Refinitiv — Free float and trading volume are collected to calculate short interest(% of float) and days to cover.

Metrics

  • Short Interest — Short interest is a strong leading indicator of market excess return. It can help monitor stock market movement.2
  • Days to Cover — Days to cover conveys information about short squeeze. High days to cover ratio signals potential short squeeze. Short squeeze occurs when a stock price jumps sharply, forcing short sellers to buy back the stock in order to limit greater loss. Detailed explanation of short squeeze can be found here.
    Melvin Capital had lost 53% of its value in late January due to GME rally, while GME days to cover had been over 2 days from mid-December,2020 to mid-January,2021, comparing to less than a day in February,2021.
